s and clinics with the task of ameliorating these disparities, Rouse argues that resources should be redirected to community-based health programs that reduce daily forms of physical and mental suffering.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDiscrimination in medical carexUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in medical carezUnited States. 0aHealth services accessibilityxUnited States. 0aHealth services accessibilityzUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxMedical carexUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxMedical carezUnited States. 0aRace discriminationxUnited States. 0aRace discriminationzUnited States. 0aSickle cell anemiaxPatientsxUnited States. 0aSickle cell anemiaxPatientszUnited States. 0aSocial medicinexUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aSocial medicinezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520945043.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles